In the first half of the NBA game between Grizzlies and Trail Blazers, scheduled for February 7 at 10:00 PM ET:

This market will resolve to "Grizzlies" if the Grizzlies are winning at halftime.

This market will resolve to "Trail Blazers" if the Trail Blazers are winning at halftime.

If the score is tied at halftime, this market will resolve 50-50.

The result will be determined based on the score at halftime only.

If the game is postponed, this market will remain open until the game has been completed. If the game is canceled entirely, with no make-up game, this market will resolve 50-50.

In the upcoming NBA game, scheduled for February 7 at 10:00 PM ET:

This market will resolve to "Trail Blazers" if the Trail Blazers win the game by 11 or more points.

If the game is postponed, this market will remain open until the game has been completed. If the game is canceled entirely, with no make-up game, this market will resolve 50-50.
